and servicemen under his command to fight courageously;

(a)  does  violence  to  any  person  bringing  any  provision  or 
supply  to  any  of  the  armed  forces  or  to  any  forces 
cooperating therewith;

(b)  irregularly detains any provision or supply being conveyed 
to any unit or other element of the armed forces or of any 
forces co-operating therewith;

(a)  steals from, or with intent to steal searches, the person of 
anyone  killed  or  wounded  in  the  course  of  warlike 
operation;

(a)  to overthrow or resist lawful authority in the armed forces 
or  in  forces  co-operating  therewith  or  in  any  part  of  the 
said forces;

(b)  absents himself without leave with intent to avoid serving 
at any place overseas or to avoid service or any particular 
service when before the enemy;

(b)  injures himself with intent thereby to render himself unfit 
for service or causes himself to be injured by any person 
with that intent;

(a)  steals  or  fraudulently  misapplies  any  public  or  service 
property  or  is  concerned  in  or  connives  at  the  stealing  or 
fraudulent misapplication of any public or service property;

(c)  loses,  or  by  negligence  damages,  any  clothing,  arms, 
ammunition or other equipment issued to him for his use 
for service purposes;

(a)  strikes or otherwise ill-treats any person who is on board a 
ship  or  aircraft  when  taken  as  prize,  or  unlawfully  takes 
from any such person anything in his possession;

(c)  refuses to produce any document in his custody or under 
his control which a court-martial has lawfully required him 
to produce;

(c)  if the corresponding civil offence is manslaughter be liable 
to imprisonment or any less punishment provided by this 
Act;

(d)  if  the  corresponding  civil  offence  is  rape  be  liable  to 
imprisonment or any less punishment provided by this Act; 
and

(f)  where  the  offender,  being  a  serviceman,  is  on  active 
service on the day of the sentence, field punishment for a 
period not exceeding ninety days;

(l)  forfeiture of good conduct medal or good conduct badges 
or  both,  either  in  addition  to  or  in  lieu  of  any  other 
punishment;

(c)  refuses to produce any document in his custody or under 
his control which a court-martial has lawfully required him 
to produce;

