before  commanding  officers  and  appropriate  superior 
authorities;

(h)  procuring  the  attendance  of  witnesses  before  courts-
martial and at the taking of evidence in pursuance of Rules 
of Procedure made under paragraph (b);

(j)  empowering  a  court-martial  or  the  convening  officer,  in 
such  cases  and  to  such  extent  as  may  be  prescribed,  to 
amend a charge which is being tried by a court-martial;

(b)  the successor of any such officer or superior officer, or any 
person for the time being exercising the functions of any 
such officer or superior officer;

